Univariate analysis was used to identify variables that have prognostic value for hospital mortality, and multivariate logistic regression analysis was used to identify variables that did not have significant prognostic value (Table 4). Identification of DAD on pathological examination (odds ratio 3.554, 95 % CI 1.385, 9.120; p = 0.008) and SOFA score on the biopsy day (odds ratio 1.424, 95 % CI 1.187, 1.707; p <0.001) were significantly and independently associated with hospital mortality. Regression coefficients for these variables were used to calculate a natural logarithm of the odds (logit) of the probability of death (p) as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
